Good. Here's the complete implementation:

---

## File to modify

**`api/operator/v1alpha1/certmanager_types.go`** — Add the CEL validation marker before the `type CertManager struct` declaration, matching the TrustManager pattern.

Change lines 180–189 from:

```go
// +genclient
// +genclient:nonNamespaced
// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object
//+kubebuilder:object:root=true
//+kubebuilder:subresource:status
//+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Cluster

// CertManager is the Schema for the certmanagers API
// +operator-sdk:csv:customresourcedefinitions:displayName="CertManager"
type CertManager struct {
```

to:

```go
// +genclient
// +genclient:nonNamespaced
// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object
//+kubebuilder:object:root=true
//+kubebuilder:subresource:status
//+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Cluster
// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule="self.metadata.name == 'cluster'",message="CertManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'"

// CertManager is the Schema for the certmanagers API
// +operator-sdk:csv:customresourcedefinitions:displayName="CertManager"
type CertManager struct {
```

The single added line is:
```
// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule="self.metadata.name == 'cluster'",message="CertManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'"
```

---

## Commands to run (in order)

```bash
cd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-treatment
make manifests
```

This regenerates:
- `config/crd/bases/operator.openshift.io_certmanagers.yaml` — the CRD will gain an `x-kubernetes-validations` entry at the top-level schema with `rule: self.metadata.name == 'cluster'`
- `bundle/manifests/operator.openshift.io_certmanagers.yaml` — the bundle copy of the CRD, updated to match

---

## What the generated CRD diff looks like

In `operator.openshift.io_certmanagers.yaml`, under `spec.versions[].schema.openAPIV3Schema`, you'll see a new block:

```yaml
x-kubernetes-validations:
- message: CertManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'
  rule: self.metadata.name == 'cluster'
```

This mirrors the existing `x-kubernetes-validations` block in `operator.openshift.io_trustmanagers.yaml`.

---

## No other files need changes

The CEL marker on the type struct is all that's needed — `make manifests` propagates it into the CRD YAML and bundle. No Go code changes are required beyond the single marker comment.
